Package org.eclipse.mosaic.fed.mapping.config.units

Class CVehicle

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.mosaic.fed.mapping.config.units.CVehicle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<CVehicle>
    public class CVehicle
extends Object
implements Comparable<CVehicle>
    Class defining a vehicle to be spawned in the simulation. Will be parsed against JSON-configuration. This class is responsible for describing the vehicles populating the simulation. It is possible to create a single vehicle (maxNumberVehicles should be one in that case) or a stream of one or multiple vehicles. The type(-s) are defined in the field types. When more than one type is defined the weights in the CPrototype can be used to balance them against each other.

      • spawningMode

        public CVehicle.SpawningMode spawningMode
        Adjusts the departure time of individual vehicles.
        See Also:
        spawns vehicles by the given targetFlow, increases the vehicle flow demand exponentially to targetFlow until maxTime is reached, decreases the vehicle flow demand exponentially from targetFlow until maxTime is reached

        public List<Integer> lanes
        List of lanes to be used. The vehicles will be evenly distributed among the given lanes. When no value is given lane zero will be used for all vehicles.

      • departSpeed

        public double departSpeed
        The speed at which the vehicle is supposed to depart. Depending on the simulator this value may only be used if departSpeedMode is set to PRECISE.

      • departSpeedMode

        public VehicleDeparture.DepartureSpeedMode departSpeedMode
        The depart speed mode. Depending on the value the depart speed behaves as follows:

        PRECISE = Use the value given in departSpeed RANDOM = The departSpeed will be overridden by a random value MAXIMUM = The departSpeed will be overridden by the max value

      • types

        public List<CPrototype> types
        List of possible vehicle types to be spawned. In this list you can simply refer to an existing CPrototype by its CPrototype.name attribute to include everything defined there. You can also overwrite every attribute of the prototype. If you don't have an existing prototype the definitions found here will be used as the prototype definition itself.

        Example configuration file: 
         {
    "prototypeDeserializers":[
        {
           "name":"PKW",
           "accel":2.5,
           "decel":4.5,
           "length":5.0,
           "minGap":2.5,
           "maxSpeed":70.0
       }
    ],
    "vehicles":[
        {
            "route":"0",
            "types":[
                { "name":"PKW" },
                {
                    "name":"PKW",
                    "accel":2.0,
                    "length":7.0
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
 }
